programme.title: Angry Planet: Blizzards

programme.title: Deadly Disasters: Tornadoes
programme.desc: The Tornado is one of Mother Nature’s most extraordinary phenomena. These intense, rapidly rotating columns of air can attain wind speeds of more than 480 kilometres per hour, and have been witnessed on every continent except Antarctica.

programme.title: Deadly Disasters: Earthquakes
programme.desc: Deadly, highly destructive and impossible to predict the Earthquake is perhaps one of Mother Nature's most terrifying forces. They flatten entire cities, create mass homelessness, and take thousands of lives. Earthquakes are truly deadly disasters.

programme.title: Deadly Disasters: Floods
programme.desc: Water may seem harmless, but in enormous quantities, it can be an astonishingly destructive force. Apart from famine, floods have resulted in more deaths worldwide than any other natural disaster.

programme.title: Deadly Disasters: Avalanches
programme.desc: We tend to think of disasters as inevitable - but often Mother Nature gives us vital clues which we foolishly ignore or overlook. This episode will take a close look at avalanches and what we can learn about how, where, and why they strike.

programme.title: Deadly Disasters: Landslides
programme.desc: Nothing can be done to prevent a landslide once it starts; they are among the most ferocious and devastating forces in nature.

programme.title: Deadly Disasters: Pandemics
programme.desc: With an ever more mobile world population, potentially growing in size to 11 billion people by the next century, public health experts agree that the possibility of a cataclysmic disease is more likely now than ever before.

programme.title: Deadly Disasters: Heatwaves
programme.desc: Temperatures in places like Saudi Arabia routinely exceed 40 degrees Celsius with very little effect on the population. However, when the same extreme heat struck the people of Russia in 2010, it killed an estimated 56,000 people.

programme.title: Deadly Disasters: Earthquakes
programme.desc: Many of our most densely populated cities are situated on the Earth’s most seismically active fault lines. Deadly, highly destructive, and impossible to predict, Earthquakes are truly one of Mother Nature’s most terrifying forces.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Land Adventures
programme.desc: Most land adventures come with some risk - a chance to confront our deepest fears, resist the pull of the ordinary, and soar into the wild unknown.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Drives
programme.desc: A journey by road expands our horizons, allowing us to explore the depth and breadth of whole countries and continents, stopping whenever and wherever we chose.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Jungle Animals
programme.desc: Encounter gorillas and orangutans, killer tree-dwelling pythons, delightful monkeys, awe-inspiring tigers, and millions of land-dwelling red crabs in Australia, the islands of Southeast Asia, Africa, and the Amazon.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Volcanoes
programme.desc: There are few sights on earth as compelling as a volcanic eruption. Volcanoes have the potential to cause death and widespread destruction in a heartbeat, but they also give rise to new life and ecosystems.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Mega Cities
programme.desc: Mega Cities provide a bustling home to populations of over 10 million. Travel from the high-density living of Shanghai and Bangkok to the sprawling cities of Delhi and Mexico City, each the backdrop for dynamic cultures.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Lost Cities
programme.desc: Once powerful and populous centers of influence, these lost cities are providing clues to how our ancestors existed in the world and remind us that ancient civilizations were not so far removed from our own.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Forest Animals
programme.desc: Forest Animals gets up close with bears, koalas, moose, wolves, weaver ants, and Tasmanian Devils. This episode roves dark forests floors and soars above vast canopies of green in America, China, Laos, and Australia.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Mountains
programme.desc: The earth’s fragile crust has folded and faulted, and nowhere are these natural forces more evident than in the world’s great mountains. Explore the highest peaks of the world’s terrain - the rugged realm between heaven and earth.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Global Cities
programme.desc: Travel to the centers of wealth, power, industry, and innovation. From London to Tokyo, Hong Kong to New York, these are the cities that never sleep. The influence held in these economic hubs unites the global community.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Archipelagos
programme.desc: The romantic notion of island life has always attracted us. Explore the histories, cultures, and unique ways of life on the World’s Greatest Archipelagos - clusters of islands that share common bonds of geography, geology, and genealogy.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Extreme Animals
programme.desc: Extreme Animals features environments hostile to humans, but havens to many animals. Witness gorgeous glow-worms, high flying condors, parched thorny devils, emperor penguins, and polar bears in this journey through life on the edge.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Marine Animals
programme.desc: From the surprises of colorful reef characters to effervescent penguins, killer sharks, and regal whales, dive into the places where nature reveals itself in some of its most marvelous and bizarre forms.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Sacred Sites
programme.desc: Ancient in architecture and detailed in design, these man-made masterpieces stand as testaments to the strength of human faith. These sites endure as a timeless reminder of resilience, respect, and the need to reflect.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Ancient Cities
programme.desc: In Ancient Cities, we journey to these ancestors of influence such as Luang Prabang, Vienna, and Istanbul where religious and cultural centers have shaped the ways in which we view the world around us and continue to do so in modern times.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Capital Cities
programme.desc: With visionaries, politicians, and activists, these metropolises are defined as the official seats of government. Dublin, Washington, and Taipei share broad avenues, museums, and monuments, but are as varied as the countries they represent.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Treks
programme.desc: Every journey made by foot promises a grand adventure. From the highest mountains to the wildest jungle realms, treks venture down the road less travelled, allowing us to connect to nature, history, and culture, one step at a time.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Monuments & Landmarks
programme.desc: Many of the world’s most significant manmade wonders serve not as dwellings, but as powerful signposts. But more than giving us direction, they tell us a story - they characterize powerful forces, or commemorate power lost.

programme.title: NEW: Secret War: The Dutch Disaster
programme.desc: Operation North Pole was a WWII German deception using captured SOE agents to mislead Britain. 47 of 50 agents were captured. Despite warnings, SOE ignored signs of compromise to maintain support, leading to a major intelligence failure.

programme.title: NEW: Secret War: The Scholar and the Fight for Greece
programme.desc: Monty Woodhouse, a professor and a legend for blowing up the Gorgopotamos Bridge in Greece in 1942. In the British counter attack against Rommell at Al Alamein in North Africa it was vital to disrupt German supply routes, Greece.
programme.sub-title: The Scholar and the Fight for Greece

programme.title: NEW: Secret War: The Banker, the Norwegians & the Bomb
programme.desc: Sir Charles attended Eton, and then joined the Coldstream Guards. He won the Military Cross on the Western Front and, having survived the war, returned to banking.
programme.sub-title: The Banker, the Norwegians & the Bomb

programme.title: NEW: Secret War: Double Agent Tricycle
programme.desc: Dusan Popov was almost certainly James Bond. Ian Fleming knew all the stories about him. Popov managed to persuade both the Germans and MI6 to keep him in the style of a millionaire businessman while performing a series of missions against the Nazis.

programme.title: NEW: Secret War: The Mafia Connection
programme.desc: Lucky Luciano, a mafia boss of the 1930s, was in jail in 1942 on charges of running prostitution rings. US intelligence services did a deal with him and he got the Italians to share intelligence on German U boat movements.

programme.title: NEW: Secret War: Hardy Amies and Operation Ratweek
programme.desc: Operation Ratweek’s existence has always been denied. However WMR has now discovered evidence that it existed and was carried out.

programme.title: NEW: Secret War: The Special Interrogation Group
programme.desc: The SIG consisted of German speaking Jewish volunteers from Palestine. They had a highly dangerous job: which was to pose as Germans behind enemy lines and extract intelligence and do acts of sabotage. Few had a long-life expectancy.

programme.title: RAF: The Royal Air Force: Battle for the Skies
programme.desc: In this programme we bring the RAF story into the modern era. Another aircraft to have extended the RAF’s capabilities is the C130 Hercules. This aircraft has proved its capabilities in countless environments from resupply, to dropping paratroopers.

programme.title: RAF: The Royal Air Force: Battle for the Skies
programme.desc: The RAF’s maritime role is often overlooked. Between the wars the RAF operated elegant flying boats to patrol the far flung corners of the Empire.

programme.title: RAF: The Royal Air Force: Battle for the Skies
programme.desc: After the war, RAF transports helped keep Berliners alive during the Soviet blockade of the city in 1948/49. As well as flying round-the-clock operations into the airport, Sunderland flying boats delivered supplies by landing on Lake Havel near the city.

programme.title: RAF: The Royal Air Force: Battle for the Skies
programme.desc: By the end of the First World War the RAF had bombers that could fly to Berlin and back. For the first time in a thousand years British civilians found themselves under direct attack - by Zeppelin airships and Gotha bombers.

programme.title: RAF: The Royal Air Force: Battle for the Skies
programme.desc: By the end of the war the RAF had aircraft that could escort bombers to targets deep inside Germany and back. With the Gloster Meteor, the RAF had also entered the ‘Jet Age’. Aircraft like the Hawker Hunter and F-86 Sabre took the RAF supersonic.

programme.title: RAF: The Royal Air Force: Battle for the Skies
programme.desc: The 1920s and 30s were uncertain times for the RAF as well as all other armed services. With peace came cuts in spending on new aircraft development.

programme.title: RAF: The Royal Air Force: Battle for the Skies
programme.desc: The series begins before WWI when military commanders struggled to understand what uses aviation might have. The Wright Brothers had been the first to fly a powered aircraft in controlled flight in 1903, but even by 1914 aircraft were still underpowered.
programme.sub-title: Useless for the Purposes of War

programme.title: Nazi Hunters: Franz Stangl & Gustav Wagner
programme.desc: Nazi Hunters examines how Nazi hunter Simon Wiesenthal tracked down fugitive war criminal Franz Stangl in Brazil. Stangl was responsible for the murder of over 800,000 people.

programme.title: Nazi Hunters: Paul Touvier
programme.desc: Nazi Hunters examines how French investigators hunted down Paul Touvier a pro-Nazi sympathizer who was responsible for murdering both Jews and resistance fighters.

programme.title: Nazi Hunters: Kurt Lischka
programme.desc: Nazi Hunters looks at how German housewife Beate Klarsfeld and her husband Serge helped track down former Paris Gestapo chief Kurt Lishka. Lishka ordered the arrest and murder of over 33,000 Jews.

programme.title: Nazi Hunters: Joseph Mengele
programme.desc: Nazi Hunters examines how Mossad agents from Israel spent nearly thirty years tracking the notorious Nazi physician Josef Mengele. After the war, Mengele flees to Argentina where he lives a relatively nondescript life.

programme.title: The Abyss: Rise And Fall of The Nazis: Genocide 1942-1944
programme.desc: Genocide 1942 - 1944: Along with Treblinka and Majdanek, Sobibor was one of the camps used in Operation Reinhard, in which the Nazis murdered almost two million people.

programme.title: The Abyss: Rise And Fall of The Nazis: Armageddon 1943-1945
programme.desc: Armageddon 1943-1945: The defeat at Stalingrad in 1943 was the turning point of the war and convinced the Nazi leadership to intensify their terror and propaganda campaigns.

programme.title: Secret Nazi Expeditions: The Lost Continent (Atlantis)
programme.desc: As the Nazis rose to power, Himmler and the SS were convinced Atlantis could be found, and instigated a series of archeological expeditions seeking uncover and exploit its secrets.

programme.title: Secret Nazi Expeditions: Walking with Witches
programme.desc: Convinced the medieval witch trials were a Judeo-Christian attempt to exterminate the Aryans, Himmler established a special team led by Reinhard Heydrich to build a database of medieval German witchcraft practices.

programme.title: Secret Nazi Expeditions: The Quest for the Holy Grail
programme.desc: Revealing the work of a secret team of scientists and scholars established by SS leader Heinrich Himmler to scour the globe seeking the origins of the Aryan race and collect ancient artifacts.
programme.sub-title: The Quest for the Holy Grail

programme.title: Secret Nazi Expeditions: Into the Mountains (Tibet)
programme.desc: Revealing the work of a secret team of scientists and scholars established by SS leader Heinrich Himmler to scour the globe seeking the origins of the Aryan race and collect ancient artifacts.

programme.title: Secret Nazi Expeditions: Cro Magnon
programme.desc: The debate about humanity's true origins becomes a nefarious fixation as SS leader Heinrich Himmler turns his attention to proving the Paleolithic past of Germany's Aryan race.

programme.title: Secret Nazi Expeditions: Runes
programme.desc: Runes are the letters of an ancient Germanic writing system that harkens back to a mythological age filled with heroes, magic, and mystery.

programme.title: Beyond The Myth: The SS Unveiled: From The "Protection Squadron" To The SS State.
programme.desc: From the Protection Squadron to the SS State: Trace the rise to power of the SS as we examine several perpetrators. Who was recruited? And why was the SS attractive to men?
programme.sub-title: From The "Protection Squadron" To The SS State.

programme.title: Beyond The Myth: The SS Unveiled: Heinrich Himmler
programme.desc: Heinrich Himmler: An agriculturalist by trade, he went on to lead the SS and tried to escape responsibility at the end of the war. Who was Heinrich Himmler?

programme.title: Beyond The Myth: The SS Unveiled: The Executioner: Reinhard Heydrich
programme.desc: The Executioner: Reinhard Heydrich: More than any other Nazi leader, Heydrich was an orchestrator of mass murder, and was terrifyingly clinical in approach.

programme.title: Beyond The Myth: The SS Unveiled: The Waffen-SS
programme.desc: The Waffen-SS: Masqueraded as military excellence, the reality was very different. Recruits were poorly trained and remorse was nonexistent, as SS troops killed mercilessly.

programme.title: Beyond The Myth: The SS Unveiled: The SS Death Head's Unit
programme.desc: The SS Death Head's Unit: Tasked with guarding concentration camps, this unit's actions knew no bounds, and, despite their heinous acts, still attended social gatherings.

programme.title: Beyond The Myth: The SS Unveiled: Unrepentant: The SS And Its Myth After 1945
programme.desc: Unrepentant: The SS and Its Myth After 1945: Drawing a line to the present, the atrocities of the SS are beyond all doubt, yet, there is a cult surrounding 'old comrades' today.
programme.sub-title: Unrepentant: The SS And Its Myth After 1945

programme.title: Hitler's Secret Sex Life: X-Rated
programme.desc: Adolf Hitler had a depraved sex life that he tried to keep hidden from the German public. He was said to be a chronic masturbator, a voyeur and that he engaged in sado-masochistic sex with women.

programme.title: Hitler's Secret Sex Life: Body Image
programme.desc: Hitler wanted the world to believe he possessed super-human qualities but in private he was a wreck. This episode reveals the archives that confirm Hitler’s genital deformity, the alarming truth about his heavy drug addiction and the Parkinson’s.

programme.title: Hitler's Secret Sex Life: Family Matters
programme.desc: Adolf Hitler's father was a violent, abusive man. His mother doted on her young son. This episode delves deep into the psychology of Hitler as the narcissistic child who grew into a malignant psychopath full of rage and deep hatred.

programme.title: Hitler's Secret Sex Life: Suicidal Maidens
programme.desc: Using extensive archival research, this program explores the squalid secrets he lied and killed to protect

programme.title: The Abyss: Rise And Fall of The Nazis: The Seeds of Violence 1918-1922
programme.desc: The Seeds of Violence 1918-1922: In the wake of the First World War, Adolf Hitler identifies Benito Mussolini as his model and has one ultimate goal: to gain power in Germany.

programme.title: December Bride
programme.desc: The last person Layla O’Reilly wants as her date to the wedding between her ex-fiancé and her own cousin is Seth Murphy, the one who introduced the soon-to-be-married couple. But it’s better than showing up alone.

programme.title: Magic Stocking
programme.desc: A young widow finds a tattered old Christmas stocking at a Holiday craft sale, but is skeptical of its magic when it seems to create small trinkets on its own.

programme.title: In Merry Measure
programme.desc: When pop star Darcy returns home to spend Christmas with her sister and niece, she unexpectedly finds herself coaching the high school choir with her onetime rival, Adam.

programme.title: The Christmas Doctor
programme.desc: Zoey is a traveling doctor who prefers short assignments to staying put, so when she is assigned to a small town clinic for the holidays, she is surprised when she starts to feel at home.

programme.title: Boyfriends of Christmas Past
programme.desc: Leading up to Christmas, marketing executive, Lauren, is visited by the ghosts of four ex boyfriends. She must learn to open her heart or risk losing her best friend, Nate.

programme.title: Holiday Hearts
programme.desc: While planning an annual Christmas party, Peyton is forced together with Ben to care for a friend's daughter. While finding their Christmas spirit, will there be some romance along the way?

programme.title: A Glenbrooke Christmas
programme.desc: Longing to be accepted for herself and not just her wealth, an heiress heads to the small town of Glenbrooke, where she discovers the joys of a simple Christmas, community, and maybe even love.

programme.title: With Love, Christmas
programme.desc: Melanie Welch is a hard-working ad executive who finds herself teamed up with uptight coworker Donovan Goodwin to come up with the ultimate Christmas commercial for a new cell phone.

programme.title: A Christmas Treasure
programme.desc: After opening a 100-year-old time capsule and meeting a charming chef, Lou questions whether or not she should move to New York after Christmas and further her writing career.

programme.title: Nantucket Noel
programme.desc: During the Seaside Noel celebrations Christina learns of a developer who is planning to tear down the wharf that is home to her toy store. Tensions rise as she falls for the developer's son, Andy.

programme.title: Mary Two-Axe Earley I Am Indian Again
programme.desc: This film shares the powerful story of Mary Two-Axe Earley, who fought for more than two decades to challenge sex discrimination against First Nations women embedded in Canada’s Indian Act and became a key figure in Canada’s women’s rights movement.

programme.title: Notmans World
programme.desc: William Notman was a man of rare talent. Photography was still in its infancy when he opened his first studio--in Montréal--in the late 1850s. He rapidly turned his art, and a budding technology, into a highly successful business.

programme.title: Nails
programme.desc: A blacksmith is seen labouring at his forge, shaping nails from single strands of steel rods. It then shifts from this setting to the roar of a twentieth-century nail mill, where machines, cut, and pound the steel rods faster than the eye can follow.

programme.title: How They Saw Us Service In The Sky
programme.desc: Made in 1957, this film glamorizes a service job in which minor emergencies appear as serious and absorbing challenges. Marriage is assumed to be the natural end of the middle-class woman's working life.

programme.title: Long Time Comin
programme.desc: There is a cultural revolution going on in Canada and Faith Nolan and Grace Channer are on the leading edge. These two African-Canadian lesbian artists give back to art its most urgent meanings--commitment and passion.

programme.title: The Tender Tale Of Cinderella Penguin
programme.desc: Medieval-style animation twists Cinderella with a mistreated penguin. Hilarity ensues when she loses her magic flipper, saved by Prince Charming. A wordless film with a unique fairy tale twist.

programme.title: How They Saw Us Wings On Her Shoulder
programme.desc: This is a 1943 recruitment film. Although it specifically promises women jobs in post-war aviation, its primary message is that women fulfill support positions "so that men might fly.

programme.title: Proudest Girl In The World, The
programme.desc: A musical recruiting film for the Canadian Women's Army Corp.

programme.title: First Stories - Two Spirited
programme.desc: This short documentary presents the empowering story of Rodney "Geeyo" Poucette's struggle against prejudice in the Indigenous community as a two spirited person (gay, lesbian, bisexual, and transgender).

programme.title: Last Chance
programme.desc: Last Chance by Paul Émile d’Entremont travels the world to tell the stories of five asylum seekers who flee their native countries to escape homophobic violence. Here in Canada, they face hurdles integrating into society and fear deportation.

programme.title: The Tree That Remembers
programme.desc: In 1992, an Iranian student took his life in Ontario, haunted despite refuge in Canada. Masoud Raouf's 'The Tree that Remembers' unites former political prisoners, honoring the dead and celebrating resilience with testimony, footage, and art.

programme.title: Adams World
programme.desc: Adam's World present a short lecture by Elizabeth Dodson Gray, a feminist theologian, environmentalist, and futurist. She speaks to us about the severity of our global environmental crisis, and analyzes the root cause of this crisis.

programme.title: Challenger An Industrial Romance
programme.desc: Follows the development of Canadair's super-executive jet. The film captures the spirit of the Canadian air transport industry and its attempt to compete with the American leaders in the industry.

programme.title: Chile Obstinate Memory
programme.desc: A generation of young Chileans has grown up with no knowledge of the facts surrounding the military coup of September 11, 1973. Now, Patricio Guzmán returns to Chile, after 23 years. The time has come to reveal the long-forgotten truth.

programme.title: Undertaker For Life!
programme.desc: Undertakers are anything but gloomy; they’re funny, generous and dedicated. We would gladly go on vacation with them, but sadly, they never have any dead time.

programme.title: Return To Vimy
programme.desc: Colourized archive footage that takes us back in time to revisit the daily lives of the soldiers of the Canadian Corps, witnessing the long and detailed preparation that lead to this legendary battle.

programme.title: Maud Lewis A World Without Shadows
programme.desc: Against a backdrop of charming paintings and the Yarmouth, Nova Scotia landscape they reflect, Maud Lewis: A World Without Shadows celebrates the life and work of one of Canada's foremost primitive painters.

programme.title: Chaque Enfant
programme.desc: This is the story of a baby who appears mysteriously on the doorstep of a busy executive, and who is subsequently bounced from household to household down the block. Nobody in the community is interested in caring for the baby without a name.

programme.title: Unarchived
programme.desc: In community archives across British Columbia, local knowledge keepers are fighting for a more inclusive history through family photos, newspaper articles and deeply rooted memories.

programme.title: Doctor Lawyer Indian Chief
programme.desc: A tribute to Indigenous women everywhere, this short documentary focuses on 5 women from across Canada. They talk about the importance of Indigenous culture in helping them to develop a sense of self and seeing through rough times.

programme.title: Kanehsatake 270 Years Of Resistance
programme.desc: In July 1990, a dispute over a proposed golf course to be built on Kanien'kéhaka (Mohawk) lands in Oka, Quebec, set the stage for an historic confrontation that would grab international headlines and sear itself into the Canadian consciousness.

programme.title: Lipsett Diaries
programme.desc: Lipsett Diaries is a descent into the maelstrom of anguish that tormented famed Canadian experimental filmmaker Arthur Lipsett, who died prematurely at age 49.

programme.title: Firewords Louky Bersianik Jovette Marchessault Nicole Brossa
programme.desc: Firewords offers an intimate glimpse of three respected, controversial Québec writers.Louky Bersianik, Jovette Marchessault and Nicole Brossard have contributed greatly to the creation of a distinctive women's literature.

programme.title: Mistelzweige küsst man nicht
programme.desc: Zu Weihnachten kehrt Darcy nach Hause zurück und läuft dort ihrem Highschool-Erzfeind Luke über den Weg. Als beide bei der Vorbereitung einer weihnachtlichen Wohltätigkeitsgala helfen, erkennen sie, dass ihre bisherige Abneigung womöglich voreilig war.

programme.title: Christmas in Boston
programme.desc: Gina und Seth sind seit ihrer Kindheit Brieffreunde, haben sich aber noch nie getroffen. Als sie sich endlich dazu entschließen, sich zu treffen, braucht es allerdings ein wenig Weihnachtszauber, um ihre Liebe füreinander aufzudecken.

programme.title: Broadcasting Christmas
programme.desc: Als ihr Sendeparyner beschliebt, Amerikas beliebteste Morgensendung zu verlassen, kundigt Veronika Daniels an, dass sie ihren neuen Co-Moderator aus einer Handvoll Kandidten auswahlen wird, zu denen auch Charlie Fisher.

programme.title: Christmas Encore
programme.desc: Charlotte Lacy ist eine verzweifelte Schauspielerin, die die Hauptrolle in einer Produktion von "A Christmas Carol" ergattert. Sie und der Regisseur haben jedoch viele unterschiedliche kreative Vorstellungen.

programme.title: Eine Hochzeit an Weihnachten
programme.desc: Haley Foster entkam ihrer Kleinstadt-Kindheit in Pineridge und baute sich ein Großstadtleben in Los Angeles als Top-Hochzeitsplanerin in einer elitären und mächtigen Firma auf, die von Frau Reynolds geleitet wird.

programme.title: Weihnachten in Alaska
programme.desc: Als die Geschäftsfrau Jennifer erfährt, dass ihre Eltern in den Ferien ohne sie unterwegs sein werden, beschließt sie, ihr geschäftiges Stadtleben in San Francisco zu verlassen, um das Gasthaus ihrer Großmutter zu besuchen.

programme.title: Der Weihnachts-Song
programme.desc: Budgetkürzungen zwingen zwei New Yorker Hochschulen zu fusionieren. Ein Musiklehrer und eine Lehrerin konkurrieren im größten Weihnachts-Song Wettbewerb des Landes um die Arbeitsstelle des...

programme.title: Christmas Land
programme.desc: Christmas Land hat seit dem tragischen Tod von Glinda schon bessere Tage gesehen, und Jules muss viele komplizierte Entscheidungen treffen.

programme.title: Die Weihnachtstruppe
programme.desc: Die arbeitslose Kunstlehrerin Allie möchte Witwer Gordon und seine Töchter wieder für Weihnachten begeistern.

programme.title: My Christmas Love
programme.desc: Celeste ist Event-Managerin, der Advent ihre Hoch-Saison. Gleichzeitig muss sie sich um ihre Nichte Finley kümmern, die bei ihr lebt. Einzige Lösung: sie engagiert Kindermädchen Taylor. Doch die entpuppt sich als Mann...

programme.title: Ein Weihnachtsmärchen
programme.desc: Ebenezer Scrooge ist herzlos und interessiert sich für nichts als seine Geschäfte. An einem Weihnachtsabend jedoch erscheint ihm der Geist eines verstorbenen Geschäftspartners Marley und warnt ihn davor, sein Leben wie bisher weiterzuleben.

programme.title: Weihnachten In Rom
programme.desc: Lacey Chabert spielt die unabhängig denkende, amerikanische Stadtführerin Angela, die kurz vor Weihnachten ihren Job in Rom verliert. Als sie auf den New Yorker Top-Manager Oliver trifft, heuert er sie als seine Stadtführerin für die Ewige Stadt an.

programme.title: Ein perfektes Weihnachten
programme.desc: Holly Maddux fehlt zu ihrem Glück nur noch der perfekte Mann. Nach einem Sturz vor dem Geschäft schwebt Holly im siebten Himmel, denn ihr Traummann steht plötzlich vor ihr...

programme.title: Hallo, ich bin der Weihnachtsmann!
programme.desc: Nachdem der Weihnachtsmann aus seinem Schlitten fällt und eine Amnesie erleidet, kann ihn nur die Unschuld eines kleinen Kindes retten.

programme.title: Weihnachten In Rom
programme.desc: Lacey Chabert spielt die unabhängig denkende, amerikanische Stadtführerin Angela, die kurz vor Weihnachten ihren Job in Rom verliert. Als sie auf den New Yorker Top-Manager Oliver trifft, heuert er sie als seine Stadtführerin für die Ewige Stadt an.

programme.title: Mein Weihnachtstraum
programme.desc: Um sich vor der gefürchteten Besitzerin eines Kaufhauses in Paris zu beweisen, bittet Managerin Christina den kürzlich gefeuerten Kurt um Hilfe in der Weihnachtszeit. Als die beiden sich näher kommen, muss Christina eine schwere Wahl treffen...

programme.title: Ein Pferd für Lizzy – Mein Freund fürs Leben
programme.desc: Die rebellische Teenagerin Lizzy wird von ihren Eltern an Weihnachten widerwillig auf die Pferderanch ihrer Großmutter geschickt. Die Großmutter weiß, dass Lizzy ein großartiges Mädchen ist und vertraut ihr die Pflege eines Pferdes namens Hope...

programme.title: Weihnachten In Rom
programme.desc: Lacey Chabert spielt die unabhängig denkende, amerikanische Stadtführerin Angela, die kurz vor Weihnachten ihren Job in Rom verliert. Als sie auf den New Yorker Top-Manager Oliver trifft, heuert er sie als seine Stadtführerin für die Ewige Stadt an.

programme.title: Weihnachtsmann aus Leidenschaft
programme.desc: Was wäre wohl, wenn der Weihnachtsmann in der Nachbarschaft leben würde? Es wäre ein Paradies für Kinder, nicht jedoch für eine junge Frau, die als Staatsanwältin tätig ist und sich für ihren Vater schämt.

programme.title: Simsalabim Sabrina: Weihnachtsstimmung
programme.desc: Es ist Weihnachten und Gems Selbstgefälligkeit macht alle verrückt. Sabrina will ihr die Augen öffnen. Sie inszeniert mit ihrer Familie eine Gespenster-Erscheinung wie in Charles Dickens' Weihnachtsgeschichte.

programme.title: Anthony Bourdain – Eine Frage des Geschmacks: Holiday Special
programme.desc: Eine Frage des Geschmacks setzt eine beliebte Festtagstradition fort – Tony erlebt ein ungewöhnliches und merkwürdiges Weihnachtsfest.

programme.title: Beverly Hills 90210: Ready Or Not
programme.desc: Dr. Monahan wirft Kelly aus der Klinik. Brandon und Steve stellen eine neue Assistentin namens Janet Sosna ein und holen David als Musikkritiker an Bord. Valerie macht einen Deal mit einem Buchmacher, der seine Geschäfte im „After Dark“ abwickelt.

programme.title: Weihnachten In Rom
programme.desc: Lacey Chabert spielt die unabhängig denkende, amerikanische Stadtführerin Angela, die kurz vor Weihnachten ihren Job in Rom verliert. Als sie auf den New Yorker Top-Manager Oliver trifft, heuert er sie als seine Stadtführerin für die Ewige Stadt an.

programme.title: Rocket Power: Schneefrei / Willkommen im Club
programme.desc: Die Kids sollen zu einer langweiligen Schulversammlung. Kurzerhand beschließen sie, dass heute schneefrei ist. / Die Kinder haben eine Probewoche im piekfeinen Ocean Shores Beach Club gewonnen! Ob das gut geht ...?!

programme.title: Bubble Guppies: Eine fröhliche Guppy-Weihnacht

programme.title: Um Anjo em Minha Vida
programme.desc: Uma jovem adolescente rica e mimada está prestes a descobrir que o verdadeiro valor não está nas etiquetas de preços e "coisas", mas nos atos gentis de ajudar os outros, tudo com a mão amiga de um anjo da guarda.

programme.title: Desejo de Natal
programme.desc: Sem dinheiro e abandonada pelo marido com três filhos, Martha não está tendo o melhor fim de ano da sua vida. Mas ela muda de cidade e redescobre a esperança quando encontra um emprego e uma rede de apoio em uma pacata lanchonete de interior.

programme.title: Natal Feliz
programme.desc: Após a morte de seu pai, um menino cria um vínculo especial com o cachorro de um vizinho e aprende a ser um homem ajudando seus avós durante uma tempestade de inverno.

programme.title: Uma Estrela no Paraíso
programme.desc: Quando um empreiteiro ameaça a vida pacífica de Noelle, ela e seus amigos usam seu dom de fazer milagres para frustrar seus planos e salvar seu vilarejo.

programme.title: Desejamos a Você um Feliz Natal
programme.desc: Na minúscula cidade de Harmony, as pessoas trabalharam tanto que esqueceram que a música existe! Em seguida, três pequenos órfãos decididos partem para encontrar um presente que possam dar aos trabalhadores da cidade.

programme.title: Tempo de Natal
programme.desc: Dois irmãos distantes tentam se reconectar no Natal, mas há algo que um deles não consegue superar: o outro pensa que é um viajante do tempo.

programme.title: Véspera de Natal
programme.desc: É véspera de Natal e um apagão vai obrigar alguns nova-iorquinos ocupados a ficarem presos dentro de elevadores enquanto esperam por ajuda. Essa longa noite juntos irá mudar suas vidas para sempre.

programme.title: O Projeto de Natal
programme.desc: Quatro irmãos unem forças para se vingar dos Hagbarts, os valentões mais malvados de sua escola.

programme.title: O Natal Prometido
programme.desc: Quando uma queda de energia causa pânico em uma loja, eles são separados um do outro. Cada um sentiu uma conexão com o outro, mas eles não têm como se reconectar. Com a aproximação do Natal, nem Kim nem Theo podem esquecer o outro.

programme.title: Lucia e o Cristal Mágico
programme.desc: Lucia é a primeira menina da Escola Internacional de Natal. Quando seu melhor amigo, Oscar, é acusado de roubar o cristal mágico do Rei Inverno, que alimenta a máquina atual, Lucia se propõe a provar a inocência dele.

programme.title: The Santa Squad
programme.desc: Allie, una profesora de arte desempleada, acepta un trabajo para ayudar a un viudo rico y a sus dos hijas. Mientras Allie levanta el espíritu navideño de la familia con adornos navideños, su amabilidad se ve recompensada con un regalo inesperado: ¡Amor!

programme.title: Homemade Christmas
programme.desc: Cada año, una joven quiere convertirse en la mejor asistente para contratar en Navidad. Pero cuando llega la oportunidad de salvar una fiesta de Navidad y deslumbrar a la persona que le gusta, deberá elegir entre sus aspiraciones y el hombre perfecto.

programme.title: Las navidades de Pete
programme.desc: Petes Christmas es una película para televisión protagonizada por Zachary Gordon y Bailee Madison. Un niño se encuentra en el centro de atención inesperado cuando se da cuenta de que el terrible día de Navidad de su familia sigue repitiéndose.

programme.title: Noche Serena: Entre el Coraje y la Fe
programme.desc: 1818 Austria, el sacerdote José, se enfrenta a una crisis antes de una elección crucial de Navidad.

programme.title: Una Navidad muy Britanica
programme.desc: El vuelo de la cantante de ópera Jessica a su concierto en Viena se retrasa y ella se queda varada en Yorkshire. El único lugar para quedarse es un bed and breakfast en un pueblo encantador dirigido por un apuesto viudo llamado Andrew.

programme.title: La mejor Navidad
programme.desc: Gloria, enfocada en su trabajo en Miami después de su divorcio, envía a sus hijos a pasar la Navidad con su exmarido en Jalisco. Lo que no imaginan es que esta decisión les va a cambiar la vida.

programme.title: A Song for Christmas
programme.desc: Charlotte es nueva en la ciudad y se da la circunstancia de que su madre ha intimado con el padre de la que parece que se va a convertir en su peor enemiga.

programme.title: Una Noche Especial
programme.desc: Catherine y Robert son unos adultos mayores que nunca pensaron que podían encontrar algo increíble entre ellos. Su encuentro es una noche especial, siendo esto el inicio de una relación para vivir una segunda oportunidad de sentir verdadero amor.

programme.title: A Vineyard Christmas
programme.desc: Heather, presentadora del popular programa de Tannin TV, está decidida a crear el episodio navideño perfecto presentando una bodega única de su ciudad natal en Vermont, pero choca con el dueño de la bodega.

programme.title: Parejas de navidad
programme.desc: Las mejores amigas Sarah, Cat y Riley se reúnen para disfrutar de la magia navideña con sus familias. Con cada amigo en una encrucijada diferente, todos tendrán que unirse para redescubrir la magia navideña que sucede en la casa de Holly Lane.

programme.desc: Allie, una profesora de arte desempleada, acepta un trabajo para ayudar a un viudo rico y a sus dos hijas. Mientras Allie levanta el espíritu navideño de la familia con adornos navideños, su amabilidad se ve recompensada con un regalo inesperado: ¡Amor!

programme.title: Homemade Christmas
programme.desc: Cada año, una joven quiere convertirse en la mejor asistente para contratar en Navidad. Pero cuando llega la oportunidad de salvar una fiesta de Navidad y deslumbrar a la persona que le gusta, deberá elegir entre sus aspiraciones y el hombre perfecto.

programme.title: Las navidades de Pete
programme.desc: Petes Christmas es una película para televisión protagonizada por Zachary Gordon y Bailee Madison. Un niño se encuentra en el centro de atención inesperado cuando se da cuenta de que el terrible día de Navidad de su familia sigue repitiéndose.

programme.title: Noche Serena: Entre el Coraje y la Fe
programme.desc: 1818 Austria, el sacerdote José, se enfrenta a una crisis antes de una elección crucial de Navidad.

programme.title: Una Navidad muy Britanica
programme.desc: El vuelo de la cantante de ópera Jessica a su concierto en Viena se retrasa y ella se queda varada en Yorkshire. El único lugar para quedarse es un bed and breakfast en un pueblo encantador dirigido por un apuesto viudo llamado Andrew.

programme.title: La mejor Navidad
programme.desc: Gloria, enfocada en su trabajo en Miami después de su divorcio, envía a sus hijos a pasar la Navidad con su exmarido en Jalisco. Lo que no imaginan es que esta decisión les va a cambiar la vida.

programme.title: A Song for Christmas
programme.desc: Charlotte es nueva en la ciudad y se da la circunstancia de que su madre ha intimado con el padre de la que parece que se va a convertir en su peor enemiga.

programme.title: Una Noche Especial
programme.desc: Catherine y Robert son unos adultos mayores que nunca pensaron que podían encontrar algo increíble entre ellos. Su encuentro es una noche especial, siendo esto el inicio de una relación para vivir una segunda oportunidad de sentir verdadero amor.

programme.title: A Vineyard Christmas
programme.desc: Heather, presentadora del popular programa de Tannin TV, está decidida a crear el episodio navideño perfecto presentando una bodega única de su ciudad natal en Vermont, pero choca con el dueño de la bodega.

programme.title: Parejas de navidad
programme.desc: Las mejores amigas Sarah, Cat y Riley se reúnen para disfrutar de la magia navideña con sus familias. Con cada amigo en una encrucijada diferente, todos tendrán que unirse para redescubrir la magia navideña que sucede en la casa de Holly Lane.

programme.title: The Santa Squad
programme.desc: Allie, una profesora de arte desempleada, acepta un trabajo para ayudar a un viudo rico y a sus dos hijas. Mientras Allie levanta el espíritu navideño de la familia con adornos navideños, su amabilidad se ve recompensada con un regalo inesperado: ¡Amor!

programme.title: Homemade Christmas
programme.desc: Cada año, una joven quiere convertirse en la mejor asistente para contratar en Navidad. Pero cuando llega la oportunidad de salvar una fiesta de Navidad y deslumbrar a la persona que le gusta, deberá elegir entre sus aspiraciones y el hombre perfecto.

programme.title: Las navidades de Pete
programme.desc: Petes Christmas es una película para televisión protagonizada por Zachary Gordon y Bailee Madison. Un niño se encuentra en el centro de atención inesperado cuando se da cuenta de que el terrible día de Navidad de su familia sigue repitiéndose.

programme.title: Noche Serena: Entre el Coraje y la Fe
programme.desc: 1818 Austria, el sacerdote José, se enfrenta a una crisis antes de una elección crucial de Navidad.

programme.title: Una Navidad muy Britanica
programme.desc: El vuelo de la cantante de ópera Jessica a su concierto en Viena se retrasa y ella se queda varada en Yorkshire. El único lugar para quedarse es un bed and breakfast en un pueblo encantador dirigido por un apuesto viudo llamado Andrew.

programme.title: La mejor Navidad
programme.desc: Gloria, enfocada en su trabajo en Miami después de su divorcio, envía a sus hijos a pasar la Navidad con su exmarido en Jalisco. Lo que no imaginan es que esta decisión les va a cambiar la vida.

programme.title: A Song for Christmas
programme.desc: Charlotte es nueva en la ciudad y se da la circunstancia de que su madre ha intimado con el padre de la que parece que se va a convertir en su peor enemiga.

programme.title: Una Noche Especial
programme.desc: Catherine y Robert son unos adultos mayores que nunca pensaron que podían encontrar algo increíble entre ellos. Su encuentro es una noche especial, siendo esto el inicio de una relación para vivir una segunda oportunidad de sentir verdadero amor.

programme.title: A Vineyard Christmas
programme.desc: Heather, presentadora del popular programa de Tannin TV, está decidida a crear el episodio navideño perfecto presentando una bodega única de su ciudad natal en Vermont, pero choca con el dueño de la bodega.

programme.title: Parejas de navidad
programme.desc: Las mejores amigas Sarah, Cat y Riley se reúnen para disfrutar de la magia navideña con sus familias. Con cada amigo en una encrucijada diferente, todos tendrán que unirse para redescubrir la magia navideña que sucede en la casa de Holly Lane.

programme.title: Lieder, Land & Leute zu Gast im Sonnenparadies Kärnten
programme.desc: Dagmar Obernosterer ist zu Gast bei Kärntner Freunden. Viele bekannte Interpreten präsentieren ihre Hits in den herrlichsten Naturlandschaften, die das schöne Kärnten zu bieten hat. Die Original Fidelen Lavanttaler, Grand-Prix-Sieger Marc Pircher oder die Jauntaler mit ihrem Hit Kärnten live? werden mit viel Schwung das Fernsehpublikum begeistern. Ob am Wörthersee, am Großglockner, im Wasserreich Kärnten oder im Nationalpark Hohe Tauern - das ist Natur, die von sich aus schon fantastische und beeindruckende Geschichten erzählt.

programme.title: Andreas Fulterer
programme.desc: Viel zu früh ist Andreas Fulterer vergangenes Jahr verstorben, mit nur 55 Jahren erlag er im Herbst 2016 einem schweren Krebsleiden. Für die Fans des Sängers, der einmal Mitglied der Kasteruther Spatzen war, ein Riesenschock. Im GoldStar TV Spezial Mein Weg? führt er mit all seinen großen Hits noch einmal durch seine geliebte Heimat Südtirol.

programme.title: Howard Carpendale LIVE
programme.desc: Seit den späten 60er-Jahren ist Howard Carpendale regelmäßiger Gast in den Single- und Albumcharts in Deutschland. Bei GoldStar TV sehen Sie einen Konzertklassiker aus der Cottbusser Stadthalle von 2001. "Alles OK" hieß damals das Motto. Charmant und gut gelaunt wie eh und je stand Howard Carpendale dort auf der Bühne und präsentierte seine großen, zeitlosen Hits.

programme.title: Nicole LIVE
programme.desc: Nicole zählt zu den erfolgreichsten deutschen Sängerinnen aller Zeiten. Die Hitparadenkönigin steht zum deutschen Schlager, zu ihren Songs und hat eine riesige Fangemeinde. Im ausverkauften Berliner Friedrichstadtpalast präsentiert die gebürtige Saarländerin ihre zahlreichen Hits im Rahmen ihrer umjubelten "Kaleidoskop" Tour.

programme.title: Unsere Wilde Schweiz, Staffel 2
programme.desc: Unendliche Wälder, eine herbe, unversehrte Natur und launisches Wetter prägen den Naturpark Waadtländer Jura. Wer einmal dort war, weiß um seinen besonderen Reiz: den der Abgeschiedenheit. Mit seinen Seen, Wäldern und von Trockenmauern geprägten Weiden steht das Naturjuwel für das ewige Zusammenspiel von Mensch und Natur. Das Grenzgebiet zu Frankreich bedeckt der riesige Risoud-Wald.

programme.title: Pinguine unter der Sonne Afrikas

programme.title: Kambodscha
programme.desc: Der Japaner Kikuo Morimoto fördert in Kambodscha die traditionelle Webkunst und verschafft mit der Anpflanzung von Maulbeerbäumen und der Herstellung hochwertiger Seidenstoffe Hunderten von Menschen ein Einkommen. Er geht wie jeden Morgen durch die Reihen der 300 Frauen, die in seiner Seiden-Weberei arbeiten. Der ehemalige Kimonomaler war vor 15 Jahren, bei seiner ersten Reise nach Phnom Penh, auf die Spur der fast ausgelöschten Tradition der Seidenweberei gestoßen. Ausgelöscht während der Diktatur der Roten Khmer und dem nachfolgenden Bürgerkrieg, unter dem Kambodscha jahrzehntelang gelitten hat. Für ihr Ziel, den neuen Menschen zu schaffen, zertrümmerten die Roten Khmer im Namen eines Steinzeit-Kommunismus alles Geistige und Sinnliche im Lande. Damit verschwand beinahe auch die einmalige Kunst der Seidenherstellung. Morimoto grub die alten Rezepturen des Färbens wieder aus: rot aus dem Saft der Lackschildläuse, braun vom Sud der Kokosnussschalen, grau durch die ausgekochten Äste des Lychee-Baums. Und er studierte die in Vergessenheit geratenen, über 1200 Jahre alten Muster. 1996 gründete er schließlich eine Weberei. Im ganzen Land konnte er nur noch ein Dutzend Weberinnen aufspüren und für sein Projekt begeistern. Sie verließen ihre Dörfer und zogen mit ihm nach Siem Reap, ...

programme.title: Die Verwandlungskünstler von Dakar
programme.desc: Dakar, die Hauptstadt Senegals: Hier zu überleben, ist für viele Menschen eine Frage der Improvisation. In vielen Vierteln hat die Not einen ganz eigenen Boom hervorgebracht: Die Menschen sammeln, was andere weggeworfen haben - und wandeln diese Abfälle in Neues? um. Wir zeigen, wie alte Konservendosen in Spielzeugautos, Lampen und Koffer verwandelt werden, Kronkorken in Körbe, Motoren in Kochtöpfe, Autoreifen in Eimer. So entstehen Gebrauchsgegenstände, aber auch Spielzeuge und Möbelstücke, die in Europa bereits als Kleinkunst gehandelt werden. Der 31-Jährige Malick Mbaye weiß zu schätzen, was andere Menschen wegwerfen: Büchsen, Dosen und Flaschendeckel - oder alte Paletten. Zusammen mit seinem Kompagnon Alassane Diop, 26, bastelt er daraus mit meist improvisierten Werkzeugen Kommoden, Koffer oder Gießkannen, aber auch Spielzeug. Sogar aus Europa erhalten die beiden inzwischen Aufträge. Mit ihrer kleinen Werkstatt Soweto Village? können sie ihre Eltern und Geschwister ernähren, für eigene Familien allerdings reicht das bescheidene Einkommen nicht. Lebenstraum der beiden ist es, eines Tages alle Freunde und Verwandte beschäftigen zu können.Schon jetzt ist ihre Veranda sozialer Mittelpunkt der Nachbarschaft. Ganze Stadtteile Dakars leben von der Müll-Verwandlung. Aus Mangel an ...

programme.title: Die Marmorberge von Italien
programme.desc: Die Apuanischen Alpen im Nordwesten der Toskana beherbergen eines der größten Marmorvorkommen der Welt. Seit der Römerzeit wird hier der weltberühmte Carrara-Marmor abgebaut. Mit allen Mitteln der Technik ringt der Mensch dem Berg das wertvolle Gestein ab und transportiert es auf halsbrecherischen Wegen ins Tal, von wo aus seine Reise in die ganze Welt beginnt. Am frühen Morgen fährt der Bildhauer Renzo Maggi zum 1.300 Meter hoch gelegenen Marmorbruch von Monte Cervaiole. Bereits Michelangelo hat sich hier im 16. Jahrhundert seine gigantischen Marmorblöcke ausgesucht. Trotz moderner Technik wird die Marmorgewinnung größtenteils noch auf traditionelle Weise betrieben. Teilweise unter lebensgefährlichen Bedingungen: Extreme Wetterschwankungen und Nebel erschweren den Einsatz von schwerem Gerät. Auf halsbrecherischen Serpentinen wird die tonnenschwere Last dann hinab zum Hafen von Carrara gebracht, von wo aus der Marmor seine Reise in die ganze Welt antritt.

programme.title: Die letzten Cowboys der Toskana
programme.desc: Im Herzen der Maremma, der Küstenregion der Toskana, werden auf einer Azienda seit mehr als 1000 Jahren Rinder und Pferde gezüchtet. Butteri, wie hier die Rinderhirten genannt werden, sind wind- und wetterfeste Kerle. Am ersten Mai steht die Merca? an, das ist der wichtigste Tag des Jahres für jeden Buttero. Dann werden die wildlebenden Kälber von den Müttern getrennt und wie anno dazumal mit Brandeisen markiert.

Er geht wie jeden Morgen durch die Reihen der 300 Frauen, die in seiner Seiden-Weberei arbeiten. Der ehemalige Kimonomaler war vor 15 Jahren, bei seiner ersten Reise nach Phnom Penh, auf die Spur der fast ausgelöschten Tradition der Seidenweberei gestoßen. Ausgelöscht während der Diktatur der Roten Khmer und dem nachfolgenden Bürgerkrieg, unter dem Kambodscha jahrzehntelang gelitten hat. Für ihr Ziel, den neuen Menschen zu schaffen, zertrümmerten die Roten Khmer im Namen eines Steinzeit-Kommunismus alles Geistige und Sinnliche im Lande. Damit verschwand beinahe auch die einmalige Kunst der Seidenherstellung. Morimoto grub die alten Rezepturen des Färbens wieder aus: rot aus dem Saft der Lackschildläuse, braun vom Sud der Kokosnussschalen, grau durch die ausgekochten Äste des Lychee-Baums. Und er studierte die in Vergessenheit geratenen, über 1200 Jahre alten Muster. 1996 gründete er schließlich eine Weberei. Im ganzen Land konnte er nur noch ein Dutzend Weberinnen aufspüren und für sein Projekt begeistern. Sie verließen ihre Dörfer und zogen mit ihm nach Siem Reap, ...

programme.title: Die Verwandlungskünstler von Dakar
programme.desc: Dakar, die Hauptstadt Senegals: Hier zu überleben, ist für viele Menschen eine Frage der Improvisation. In vielen Vierteln hat die Not einen ganz eigenen Boom hervorgebracht: Die Menschen sammeln, was andere weggeworfen haben - und wandeln diese Abfälle in Neues? um. Wir zeigen, wie alte Konservendosen in Spielzeugautos, Lampen und Koffer verwandelt werden, Kronkorken in Körbe, Motoren in Kochtöpfe, Autoreifen in Eimer. So entstehen Gebrauchsgegenstände, aber auch Spielzeuge und Möbelstücke, die in Europa bereits als Kleinkunst gehandelt werden. Der 31-Jährige Malick Mbaye weiß zu schätzen, was andere Menschen wegwerfen: Büchsen, Dosen und Flaschendeckel - oder alte Paletten. Zusammen mit seinem Kompagnon Alassane Diop, 26, bastelt er daraus mit meist improvisierten Werkzeugen Kommoden, Koffer oder Gießkannen, aber auch Spielzeug. Sogar aus Europa erhalten die beiden inzwischen Aufträge. Mit ihrer kleinen Werkstatt Soweto Village? können sie ihre Eltern und Geschwister ernähren, für eigene Familien allerdings reicht das bescheidene Einkommen nicht. Lebenstraum der beiden ist es, eines Tages alle Freunde und Verwandte beschäftigen zu können.Schon jetzt ist ihre Veranda sozialer Mittelpunkt der Nachbarschaft. Ganze Stadtteile Dakars leben von der Müll-Verwandlung. Aus Mangel an ...

programme.title: Die Marmorberge von Italien
programme.desc: Die Apuanischen Alpen im Nordwesten der Toskana beherbergen eines der größten Marmorvorkommen der Welt. Seit der Römerzeit wird hier der weltberühmte Carrara-Marmor abgebaut. Mit allen Mitteln der Technik ringt der Mensch dem Berg das wertvolle Gestein ab und transportiert es auf halsbrecherischen Wegen ins Tal, von wo aus seine Reise in die ganze Welt beginnt. Am frühen Morgen fährt der Bildhauer Renzo Maggi zum 1.300 Meter hoch gelegenen Marmorbruch von Monte Cervaiole. Bereits Michelangelo hat sich hier im 16. Jahrhundert seine gigantischen Marmorblöcke ausgesucht. Trotz moderner Technik wird die Marmorgewinnung größtenteils noch auf traditionelle Weise betrieben. Teilweise unter lebensgefährlichen Bedingungen: Extreme Wetterschwankungen und Nebel erschweren den Einsatz von schwerem Gerät. Auf halsbrecherischen Serpentinen wird die tonnenschwere Last dann hinab zum Hafen von Carrara gebracht, von wo aus der Marmor seine Reise in die ganze Welt antritt.

programme.title: Stochelo Rosenberg & Peter Beets
programme.desc: The treasured compositions of guitarist Django Reinhardt, the founding father of hot club jazz, are engraved in everyone's memory. Although Reinhardt missed two fingers of his left hand, his virtuoso technique was unrivalled. Dutch guitarist Stochelo Rosenberg and pianist Peter Beets now have the pleasure to bring Django's music back to life with their infectious improvisations.

programme.title: Wes Montgomery
programme.sub-title: Herbie Man & Sonny Sharrock - Memphis underground
programme.desc: This selection of unforgettable performances by some of the most iconic and influential jazz guitarists in history showcases these legends' unique essence. Revel in Wes Montgomery's virtuosity as he performs the captivating “Nica's Dream” in Holland in 1965, and delight in the expressive beauty of his rendition of “Here's That Rainy Day”, recorded in London in that same year. Experience the timeless appeal of Joe Pass's “You Stepped Out of a Dream” and “You Turned The Tables on Me”, recorded live in Hanover in 1975. The interplay between Jim Hall and Atilla Zoller borders on the impossible as they perform “Extensions” in Hanover in 1973. Enjoy Jim Hall's lyrical solo performance of “I'm Getting Sentimental Over You” from 1964. Witness Sonny Sharrock's avant-garde fusion of jazz and rock in an exhilarating performance of “Peanut", recorded live in France in 1970. Sharrock is joined by flutist Herbie Mann in a soulful performance of “Memphis Underground” from 1969. Immerse yourself in the magic of jazz guitar!

programme.title: Gilberto Gil
programme.desc: Brazilian artist Gilberto Gil returns to Jazz à Vienne in France with a new round of singing that is inspired by his latest album ‘Fé na Festa': a mixture of celebration, tradition and even some rock now and then. Gilberto Gil, worldwide known for as musician and the Brazilian minister of Culture, was one of the pioneers of the cultural movement ‘tropicalismo'. This movement, with a strong character of social protest, combines elements of traditional Brazilian culture with modern art forms. Gilberto Gil's new sound clearly has its roots in Brazilian culture, yet it is always inspired by jazz.

programme.title: Oscar Peterson Trio, Stuff Smith & Ella Fitzgerald
programme.sub-title: O.P. Trio and E. Fitz. - Jazz At The Philharmonic
programme.desc: The Royal Concertgebouw in Amsterdam is a world-renowned concert hall, known for its first-rate acoustics. It has attracted many famous performers over the years and is one of the Netherlands' most treasured musical institutions. On May 5, 1957, jazz impresario Norman Granz presented his Jazz at the Philharmonic tour at the Concertgebouw in Amsterdam. The Canadian pianist Oscar Peterson and his trio of guitarist Herb Ellis and bassist Ray Brown are later joined by trumpeter Roy Eldridge and drummer Jo Jones. As an added attraction, American violinist Stuff Smith joins the proceedings. American singer Ella Fitzgerald, accompanied by pianist Don Abney, Ellis, Brown and Jones, hits her vocal peak in a stunning set that culminates in a jam session of It Don't Mean A Thing (If It Ain't Got That Swing) with the entire ensemble.

programme.title: Robert Glasper & Jason Moran
programme.sub-title: La Gaité Lyrique: Robert Glasper & Jason Moran
programme.desc: As part of the Blue Note Jazz Festival and Blue Note Records' 75th anniversary, pianists Robert Glasper and Jason Moran delivered a stunning jazz piano duet, resulting in an exciting exploration of the great history of jazz. An intricate knowledge of African-American music is infused with modern energy. The two musicians reinterpret the stride piano tradition through captivating original songs and personal interpretations of the music of Albert Ammons, Andrew Hill, Thelonious Monk, Ornette Coleman and Herbie Hancock.

programme.title: Christian Scott
programme.desc: In 2019, the vibrant city of Sofia, Bulgaria, hosted the International A to JazZ Festival. Among the featured acts was the trailblazing jazz trumpeter Christian Scott aTunde Adjuah. This genre-defying artist captivated the audience with his eclectic “stretch music” an approach that incorporates hip-hop and reaches back through the American canon into African percussion and its rich melodic content. Trumpeter Christian Scott aTunde Adjuah's quintet, which includes drummer Corey Fonville, percussionist Weedie Braimah, pianist Lawrence Fields, and bass guitarist Max Mucha, delivered a performance that defied boundaries and expectations.

programme.title: Steve Gadd
programme.desc: Many of pianist Chick Corea's compositions have become jazz standards. As a member of Miles Davis' band in the late 1960s, he participated in the birth of the electric jazz fusion movement. In the 1970s, Corea founded the legendary jazz fusion group Return to Forever. Along with Herbie Hancock, McCoy Tyner and Keith Jarrett, Corea is one of the biggest modern jazz pianists. He continued musical collaborations with a diverse range of artists, exploring various musical styles. This broadcast features three performances that illustrate Chick Corea's many talents.

programme.title: Kirill Karabits, Russian National Orchestra & Mikhail Pletnev
programme.desc: Pianist Mikhail Pletnev is accompanied by the Russian National Orchestra led by Kirill Karabits in a performance of Camille Saint-Saëns's Piano Concerto No. 2, Op. 22. At its premiere in 1868, the orchestra was led by Anton Rubinstein, with the composer himself at the piano. The current concert was recorded at the Moscow Philharmonic Society and opens with a performance of Sergei Prokofiev's symphonic picture 'Dreams'. The concert was part of the Ninth Russian National Orchestra Grand Festival from 2017.

programme.title: Ballet of the Mariinsky Theatre
programme.desc: 'La Bayadère' is a three-act ballet by the French choreographer Marius Petipa. Set in 19th-century India, 'La Bayadère' tells the sad love story of the noble warrior Solor and his Nikia, a temple dancer or 'bayadère', who is poisoned by her rival, Gamzatti. The ballet features one of the most celebrated scenes of classical ballet, namely 'The Kingdom of the Shades'. In this iconic scene, Solor dreams, under the influence of opium, of reuniting with his beloved Nikia. This production of the ballet features the revised choreography by Vladimir Ponomarev and Vakhtang Chabukiani (1941), and includes dances by Konstantin Sergeyev and Nikolai Zubkovsky. The ballet's music, composed by Ludwig Minkus, is performed by the Mariinsky Orchestra under the direction of Boris Gruzin. Among the performers are Viktoria Tereshkina, Anastasia Matvienko, Vladimir Shklyarov, and Vladimir Ponomarev. This performance was recorded at the Mariinsky Theatre in St. Petersburg, Russia, in July 2014.

programme.title: Marina De Liso, Roberto Loreggian & Nicola Dal Maso
programme.sub-title: Vocal works by Monteverdi, Frescobaldi a. o.
programme.desc: The six-concert series “Io suono italiano” is dedicated to music of Italian composers and performed by Italian musicians on Italian instruments. The concert programs cover four centuries of music: from Girolamo Frescobaldi and Antonio Vivaldi to more contemporary music by Ennio Morricone and Azio Corghi. Each program presents more familiar pieces alongside lesser-known compositions. These performances were filmed at the atmospheric Teatro Sociale in Rovigo, Italy, in January 2021. In this program, Marina De Liso (soprano), Roberto Loreggian (harpsichord), and Nicola Dal Maso (violone) present vocal Baroque music. On the program are Benedetto Ferrari's Amanti io vi so dire, Barbara Strozzi's Lamento, Tradimento, and Che si può fare, Giovanni Felice Sances's Usurpator tiranno, Girolamo Frescobaldi's Partite sopra il Passacagli, and Se l'aura spira, Claudio Monteverdi's Ohimè ch'io cado, and Si dolce è il tormento.

programme.title: Chen Xue-Hong, Zhang Cheng, Chen Yunjie & Chen Sa
programme.sub-title: Piano works by Chopin, Scriabin, Schumann & Liszt
programme.desc: In recent years, a new generation of Chinese pianists has emerged on the international scene. But there are many more young Chinese artists, who the Académie France-Chine aims to enable to deepen their art by introducing them to and giving them a platform within French and European culture. Four of these artists are Chen Xue-Hong, Zhang Cheng, Chen Yunjie and Chen Sa, who made their joint debut in Paris in this unique concert at the Théâtre des Champs-Élysées that showcased their extraordinary talent. On the program are Chopin's Piano Sonata No. 2, Schumann's Piano Sonata No. 1, Scriabin's Piano Sonata No. 8 and Paysage (No. 3) and Mazeppa (No. 4) from Liszt's Études d'Exécution Transcendante. The concert closes with Messiaen's Regard de l'Esprit de la joie (No. 10) from Vingt regards sur l'Enfant-Jésus.

programme.desc: Dagmar Obernosterer ist zu Gast bei Kärntner Freunden. Viele bekannte Interpreten präsentieren ihre Hits in den herrlichsten Naturlandschaften, die das schöne Kärnten zu bieten hat. Die Original Fidelen Lavanttaler, Grand-Prix-Sieger Marc Pircher oder die Jauntaler mit ihrem Hit Kärnten live? werden mit viel Schwung das Fernsehpublikum begeistern. Ob am Wörthersee, am Großglockner, im Wasserreich Kärnten oder im Nationalpark Hohe Tauern - das ist Natur, die von sich aus schon fantastische und beeindruckende Geschichten erzählt.

programme.title: Howard Carpendale LIVE

Bei GoldStar TV sehen Sie einen Konzertklassiker aus der Cottbusser Stadthalle von 2001. "Alles OK" hieß damals das Motto. Charmant und gut gelaunt wie eh und je stand Howard Carpendale dort auf der Bühne und präsentierte seine großen, zeitlosen Hits.

programme.title: Kambodscha
programme.desc: Der Japaner Kikuo Morimoto fördert in Kambodscha die traditionelle Webkunst und verschafft mit der Anpflanzung von Maulbeerbäumen und der Herstellung hochwertiger Seidenstoffe Hunderten von Menschen ein Einkommen. Er geht wie jeden Morgen durch die Reihen der 300 Frauen, die in seiner Seiden-Weberei arbeiten. Der ehemalige Kimonomaler war vor 15 Jahren, bei seiner ersten Reise nach Phnom Penh, auf die Spur der fast ausgelöschten Tradition der Seidenweberei gestoßen. Ausgelöscht während der Diktatur der Roten Khmer und dem nachfolgenden Bürgerkrieg, unter dem Kambodscha jahrzehntelang gelitten hat. Für ihr Ziel, den neuen Menschen zu schaffen, zertrümmerten die Roten Khmer im Namen eines Steinzeit-Kommunismus alles Geistige und Sinnliche im Lande. Damit verschwand beinahe auch die einmalige Kunst der Seidenherstellung. Morimoto grub die alten Rezepturen des Färbens wieder aus: rot aus dem Saft der Lackschildläuse, braun vom Sud der Kokosnussschalen, grau durch die ausgekochten Äste des Lychee-Baums. Und er studierte die in Vergessenheit geratenen, über 1200 Jahre alten Muster. 1996 gründete er schließlich eine Weberei. Im ganzen Land konnte er nur noch ein Dutzend Weberinnen aufspüren und für sein Projekt begeistern. Sie verließen ihre Dörfer und zogen mit ihm nach Siem Reap, ...

programme.title: Die Verwandlungskünstler von Dakar
programme.desc: Dakar, die Hauptstadt Senegals: Hier zu überleben, ist für viele Menschen eine Frage der Improvisation. In vielen Vierteln hat die Not einen ganz eigenen Boom hervorgebracht: Die Menschen sammeln, was andere weggeworfen haben - und wandeln diese Abfälle in Neues? um. Wir zeigen, wie alte Konservendosen in Spielzeugautos, Lampen und Koffer verwandelt werden, Kronkorken in Körbe, Motoren in Kochtöpfe, Autoreifen in Eimer. So entstehen Gebrauchsgegenstände, aber auch Spielzeuge und Möbelstücke, die in Europa bereits als Kleinkunst gehandelt werden. Der 31-Jährige Malick Mbaye weiß zu schätzen, was andere Menschen wegwerfen: Büchsen, Dosen und Flaschendeckel - oder alte Paletten. Zusammen mit seinem Kompagnon Alassane Diop, 26, bastelt er daraus mit meist improvisierten Werkzeugen Kommoden, Koffer oder Gießkannen, aber auch Spielzeug. Sogar aus Europa erhalten die beiden inzwischen Aufträge. Mit ihrer kleinen Werkstatt Soweto Village? können sie ihre Eltern und Geschwister ernähren, für eigene Familien allerdings reicht das bescheidene Einkommen nicht. Lebenstraum der beiden ist es, eines Tages alle Freunde und Verwandte beschäftigen zu können.Schon jetzt ist ihre Veranda sozialer Mittelpunkt der Nachbarschaft. Ganze Stadtteile Dakars leben von der Müll-Verwandlung. Aus Mangel an ...

programme.title: Die Marmorberge von Italien
programme.desc: Die Apuanischen Alpen im Nordwesten der Toskana beherbergen eines der größten Marmorvorkommen der Welt. Seit der Römerzeit wird hier der weltberühmte Carrara-Marmor abgebaut. Mit allen Mitteln der Technik ringt der Mensch dem Berg das wertvolle Gestein ab und transportiert es auf halsbrecherischen Wegen ins Tal, von wo aus seine Reise in die ganze Welt beginnt. Am frühen Morgen fährt der Bildhauer Renzo Maggi zum 1.300 Meter hoch gelegenen Marmorbruch von Monte Cervaiole. Bereits Michelangelo hat sich hier im 16. Jahrhundert seine gigantischen Marmorblöcke ausgesucht. Trotz moderner Technik wird die Marmorgewinnung größtenteils noch auf traditionelle Weise betrieben. Teilweise unter lebensgefährlichen Bedingungen: Extreme Wetterschwankungen und Nebel erschweren den Einsatz von schwerem Gerät. Auf halsbrecherischen Serpentinen wird die tonnenschwere Last dann hinab zum Hafen von Carrara gebracht, von wo aus der Marmor seine Reise in die ganze Welt antritt.

programme.title: Die letzten Cowboys der Toskana
programme.desc: Im Herzen der Maremma, der Küstenregion der Toskana, werden auf einer Azienda seit mehr als 1000 Jahren Rinder und Pferde gezüchtet. Butteri, wie hier die Rinderhirten genannt werden, sind wind- und wetterfeste Kerle. Am ersten Mai steht die Merca? an, das ist der wichtigste Tag des Jahres für jeden Buttero. Dann werden die wildlebenden Kälber von den Müttern getrennt und wie anno dazumal mit Brandeisen markiert.

programme.title: Just Cooking | Trailer
programme.desc: Just Cooking bringt Kochbegeisterten das einzigartige Paket an frischen neuen Food-Trends und junger Kreativität auf den TV. Aber auch Klassiker und traditionelle Küche, sowie kulinarische Dokumentationen und Reisevlogs werden gezeigt.

programme.desc: Los Bentheim-Tecklenburg, una dinastía noble de Renania del Norte-Westfalia, residen en el castillo de Rheda, su hogar ancestral de más de 100 habitaciones. En la actualidad, el príncipe heredero Maximilian y su esposa Marissa, junto a sus hijos, mantienen viva esta historia. Con acceso exclusivo a archivos privados, Jobst Knigge revela una mirada íntima a su legado europeo.

programme.title: Dinastías Alemanas
programme.desc: Ninguna otra dinastía está más estrechamente ligada al destino de Alemania que la de los Hohenzollern. De esta familia salieron príncipes, reyes y emperadores. Hace cien años, en noviembre de 1918, su reinado llegó a su fin. ¿Cómo afrontan los descendientes el legado de sus antepasados? ¿Qué caminos han tomado? La propia familia proporciona las respuestas. En la película, Georg Friedrich, Príncipe de Prusia, y Karl Friedrich, Príncipe de Hohenzollern, ofrecen en exclusiva una visión personal de la familia.

programme.desc: El documental explora la compleja y tumultuosa relación entre dos de las reinas más icónicas de Inglaterra: Isabel I y María I. La película examina sus vidas, destacando la intensa rivalidad y las personalidades contrastantes de las hermanas, quienes eran ambas hijas de Enrique VIII, pero nacidas de diferentes madres: Isabel de Ana Bolena y María de Catalina de Aragón.

programme.title: Miracles of Nature
programme.desc: Il viaggio di oggi alla ricerca di altri miracoli della natura ci porta nel distretto dei laghi della Masuria, un impressionante mondo acquatico nel nord-est della Polonia. Scambieremo poi la fresca regione del Baltico con i Caraibi tropicali. Qui dimostreremo che sarebbe sbagliato collegare la provincia cubana di Guantanamo solo alla famosa base navale americana. Per concludere, torneremo nella regione mediterranea dell'Europa per visitare gli abitanti delle Isole Lipari, che continuano a sopravvivere all'ombra di vulcani sempre in fiamme.

programme.title: Gold Fever

programme.title: Alaska's Wild Gourmet
programme.desc: Negli angoli più remoti del bush dell'Alaska si trova una ricchezza diversa da qualsiasi altra. Robusta, cruda e ora anche cotta, questa è l'ultima frontiera culinaria dove uno chef sta ridefinendo il significato di mangiare come un uomo selvaggio. Clienti schizzinosi, cambiamenti climatici bipolari, carenze di cibo e di forniture spesso spingono Bradley all'ultimo grammo della sua sanità mentale, ma questo spirito libero e creativo sembra sempre mantenere la promessa.

programme.title: Sasquatch Mountain Man

programme.title: Desperate Hours
programme.desc: A volte, tutto ciò che serve è uno spostamento sotto i piedi.... Desperate Hours analizza i principali disastri geologici, tra cui le valanghe in Afghanistan, Pakistan, Nepal, Perù e Francia. Vengono inoltre analizzate le frane geologiche nelle Filippine, in India e in Colombia e un'enorme voragine che ha consumato un laghetto in Bosnia. Vengono inoltre analizzate le bufere di neve negli Stati Uniti, in Israele e nel Regno Unito.

programme.title: Wild Ones
programme.desc: Non vorresti essere morso da nessuno di questi, ma qual è quello con il veleno più letale? Il veleno del serpente più velenoso del pianeta? Una rara lucertola velenosa? Oppure il polpo dagli anelli blu?

programme.title: Miracles of Nature
programme.desc: In questo episodio visitiamo luoghi in cui le persone non hanno avuto vita facile. Nonostante le difficoltà che vivono quotidianamente, scelgono di restare e di plasmare il loro destino. Bamiyan - una provincia afghana colpita dalla povertà e messa a dura prova dal tempo. programme.desc: 한국 음식의 맛은 장이 결정한다고 할 정도로 옛 조상들은 장맛이 좋지 않으면 좋은 재료를 사용해도 좋은 요리가 될 수 없다고 하였습니다. 콩 재배, 메주 만들기, 장 만들기, 장 가르기, 숙성과 발효 등으로 이어지는 중국이나 일본과 구별되는 우리나라의 독특한 제작과정을 영상으로 만나보세요. (이정숙 / 국가무형문화재 조선왕조궁중음식 이수자)자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널

programme.title: 돌에 생명을 불어넣다. 벼루장
programme.desc: 자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널벼루는 물을 붓고 먹을 가는 돌을 말합니다. 일반적으로 벼루하면 검은 남포석 벼루를 떠올리지만, 단양 자석벼루는 원석의 색이 붉은색을 띄기 때문에 자석벼루라 부르게 되었습니다. 자석벼루장인의 집요하고 끈기있는 벼루 제작과정을 만나보시죠. (신재민 / 충북무형문화재 자석벼루장 전승교육사)

programme.title: 천년의 종이를 만드는 마법. 한지뜨기
programme.desc: 자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널한지는 고도의 기술과 장인의 오랜 경험을 바탕으로 완성됩니다. 닥나무를 베고, 찌고, 삶고, 말리고, 벗기고, 다시 삶고, 두들기고, 섞고, 뜨고, 말리는 99번의 손질 후 마지막 사람이 백번째로 만진다 하여 옛사람들은 한지를 '백지(百紙)'라 부르기도 하였습니다. 장인의 정성이 담겨있는 '한지뜨기' 과정을 만나보시죠. (안치용 / 국가무형문화재 한지장 보유자)

programme.title: 종이에 염원을 담다. 지화장
programme.desc: 자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널오래전부터 궁중은 물론, 사가의 잔치, 불교의식, 굿 등에 이르기까지 지화를 사용해 왔습니다. 지화장은 종이를 오려 장식을 해 의식에 사용하기 위한 장엄을 만드는 장인을 말합니다. 한지를 염색하고 오리고 접어 전통 지화의 전승을 묵묵히 이어가는 장인의 섬세한 손기술을 소개합니다. (석용 스님 / 경기무형문화재 지화장 보유자)

programme.title: 기품있는 한옥의 멋. 고택의 하루
programme.desc: 자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널해 뜨기 전 너른 마당을 빗자루로 쓰는 소리, 어머니의 밥 짓는 정지의 풍경, 타닥타닥 장작개비가 타들어 가는 아궁이의 소리 등 지친 일상 속에서 하루쯤 푸근하게 쉬어가고 싶은 550년 역사를 자랑하는 오래된 고택에서 다양한 일상의 풍경을 이른 아침부터 밤까지 생생하게 들려드립니다. ※ 안동 진성이씨 온혜파 종택 (국가민속문화재 제295호)

programme.title: 정성과 인내의 흔적. 명주짜기
programme.desc: 자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널우리나라는 이미 신라 시대에 견직물을 당나라에 보낼 만큼 그 기술이 뛰어났으며, 명주는 전통 직조과정에서 가장 많이 생산되었던 직물입니다. 뽕나무를 재배하고 누에를 치는 일부터, 실을 뽑고 타래를 만들고, 베틀에서 한 필의 명주를 짜기까지. 전통 길쌈의 고된 노동 속에서 정성과 인내의 흔적을 만나봅시다. (두산손명주연구회 / 국가무형문화재 명주짜기 보유단체)

programme.title: 인고의 시간을 이겨내다. 털 고르기
programme.desc: 자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널필장은 문방사우(文房四友)의 하나인 붓을 만드는 장인입니다. 전통 붓 제작 과정에서 좋은 붓을 만들기 위해서는 털을 고르는 '정모 작업'이 필수적인데요. 수천 번의 손길을 거쳐야 완성되는 전통 붓의 정성을 함께 감상해보시죠. (유필무 / 충북무형문화재 필장 보유자)

programme.title: 소리의 맥을 잇다, 대금장
programme.desc: 대금은 대나무에 구멍을 뚫어 소리를 내는 관악기로, 옛 사대부들의 풍류를 상징하는 한국의 대표적인 전통악기 중 하나입니다. 대금 제작자들은 스스로 악기를 연주할 수 있는 대금 연주자이기도 한데요. 실제 연주자로서도 활발하게 활동하며 대금장으로서 전통의 맥을 잇고 있는 장인의 작업과정을 따라가 보시죠.(이정대 / 인천광역시 무형문화재 대금장 보유자)자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널

programme.title: 어부, 늪의 소리를 담다. 우포늪
programme.desc: 자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널우포늪엔 얼마만큼의 시간이 흘렀을까, 강물이 내어준 곳에 자연이 들어차고 그 주인으로 온갖 생명들이 살고 있습니다. 보이지 않지만 무수한 분초가 흐르듯 우포늪의 계절이 흐르는 소리는 신비롭죠. 들리나요? 보일듯 보이지 않는 무수한 반짝거림. 일렁임. 찰랑거림. 그 모든 시간의 자연이 조화롭게 돌아가는 소리. ※ 경상남도 창녕군 우포늪 (천연기념물 제524호)

programme.title: 풍요로운 다과 한상. 궁중병과 가을상
programme.desc: 성큼 다가온 가을과 딱 맞는 궁중병과 가을차림상, 풍요로운 과실을 가득 담은 꽃송편, 가을하면 빠질 수 없는 밤과 대추를 맛있게 졸인 숙실과(생란, 율란, 조란), 그리고 환절기 감기를 물리쳐줄 달달하고 따뜻한 배숙을 준비했습니다. 우리모두 눈으로 먹으러가요! (박영미 / 국가무형문화재 조선왕조궁중음식 이수자)자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널

programme.title: 바다가 만든 한 그릇. 통영 너물비빔밥
programme.desc: 자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널다양한 지역에 전통 비빔밥이 있지만 통영의 비빔밥은 생김새부터 남다릅니다. 제사 음식에서 비롯했기 때문인지 두부탕국을 곁들이는데요. 또한 해조류가 매우 풍부해 생미역과 톳나물을 비빔밥의 주재료로 이용합니다. 이외에도 계절에 따라 오이, 박, 미나리, 쑥갓 등 10가지 이상의 나물을 넣어 만든 통영의 풍성한 향토음식을 ASMR로 만나보세요. (이상희 / 전통음식문화연구가)

programme.title: 전통을 지키는 인내. 옹기장
programme.desc: 자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널한국인의 집집마다 적게는 네다섯 개부터 많게는 수십 개씩 가지고 있던 옹기는 한국 도자기 역사상 가장 오랜 전통을 지니고 있으며 널리 쓰이던 생활용기입니다. 옹기장 보유자가 만들어 내는 옹기의 전 제작과정을 지켜보고, 전통을 꿋꿋이 지키며 빚어온 옹기에 쏟는 정성과 인내를 배워봅시다. (정윤석, 정영균 / 국가무형문화재 옹기장 보유자, 이수자)

programme.title: [창덕궁 봄꽃 개화 현장] 봄꽃의 향연, 창덕궁 나들이

programme.title: Stochelo Rosenberg & Peter Beets
programme.desc: The treasured compositions of guitarist Django Reinhardt, the founding father of hot club jazz, are engraved in everyone's memory. Although Reinhardt missed two fingers of his left hand, his virtuoso technique was unrivalled. Dutch guitarist Stochelo Rosenberg and pianist Peter Beets now have the pleasure to bring Django's music back to life with their infectious improvisations.

programme.title: Wes Montgomery
programme.sub-title: Herbie Man & Sonny Sharrock - Memphis underground
programme.desc: This selection of unforgettable performances by some of the most iconic and influential jazz guitarists in history showcases these legends' unique essence. Revel in Wes Montgomery's virtuosity as he performs the captivating “Nica's Dream” in Holland in 1965, and delight in the expressive beauty of his rendition of “Here's That Rainy Day”, recorded in London in that same year. Experience the timeless appeal of Joe Pass's “You Stepped Out of a Dream” and “You Turned The Tables on Me”, recorded live in Hanover in 1975. The interplay between Jim Hall and Atilla Zoller borders on the impossible as they perform “Extensions” in Hanover in 1973. Enjoy Jim Hall's lyrical solo performance of “I'm Getting Sentimental Over You” from 1964. Witness Sonny Sharrock's avant-garde fusion of jazz and rock in an exhilarating performance of “Peanut", recorded live in France in 1970. Sharrock is joined by flutist Herbie Mann in a soulful performance of “Memphis Underground” from 1969. Immerse yourself in the magic of jazz guitar!

programme.title: Gilberto Gil
programme.desc: Brazilian artist Gilberto Gil returns to Jazz à Vienne in France with a new round of singing that is inspired by his latest album ‘Fé na Festa': a mixture of celebration, tradition and even some rock now and then. Gilberto Gil, worldwide known for as musician and the Brazilian minister of Culture, was one of the pioneers of the cultural movement ‘tropicalismo'. This movement, with a strong character of social protest, combines elements of traditional Brazilian culture with modern art forms. Gilberto Gil's new sound clearly has its roots in Brazilian culture, yet it is always inspired by jazz.

programme.desc: An extraordinary collection of clips in all jazz genres from the most beautiful concerts and the most special festivals, performed by the finest jazz musicians.

programme.title: Oscar Peterson Trio, Stuff Smith & Ella Fitzgerald
programme.sub-title: O.P. Trio and E. Fitz. - Jazz At The Philharmonic
programme.desc: The Royal Concertgebouw in Amsterdam is a world-renowned concert hall, known for its first-rate acoustics. It has attracted many famous performers over the years and is one of the Netherlands' most treasured musical institutions. On May 5, 1957, jazz impresario Norman Granz presented his Jazz at the Philharmonic tour at the Concertgebouw in Amsterdam. The Canadian pianist Oscar Peterson and his trio of guitarist Herb Ellis and bassist Ray Brown are later joined by trumpeter Roy Eldridge and drummer Jo Jones. As an added attraction, American violinist Stuff Smith joins the proceedings. American singer Ella Fitzgerald, accompanied by pianist Don Abney, Ellis, Brown and Jones, hits her vocal peak in a stunning set that culminates in a jam session of It Don't Mean A Thing (If It Ain't Got That Swing) with the entire ensemble.

programme.desc: As part of the Blue Note Jazz Festival and Blue Note Records' 75th anniversary, pianists Robert Glasper and Jason Moran delivered a stunning jazz piano duet, resulting in an exciting exploration of the great history of jazz. An intricate knowledge of African-American music is infused with modern energy. The two musicians reinterpret the stride piano tradition through captivating original songs and personal interpretations of the music of Albert Ammons, Andrew Hill, Thelonious Monk, Ornette Coleman and Herbie Hancock.

programme.title: Christian Scott
programme.desc: In 2019, the vibrant city of Sofia, Bulgaria, hosted the International A to JazZ Festival. Among the featured acts was the trailblazing jazz trumpeter Christian Scott aTunde Adjuah. This genre-defying artist captivated the audience with his eclectic “stretch music” an approach that incorporates hip-hop and reaches back through the American canon into African percussion and its rich melodic content. Trumpeter Christian Scott aTunde Adjuah's quintet, which includes drummer Corey Fonville, percussionist Weedie Braimah, pianist Lawrence Fields, and bass guitarist Max Mucha, delivered a performance that defied boundaries and expectations.

programme.title: Steve Gadd
programme.desc: Many of pianist Chick Corea's compositions have become jazz standards. As a member of Miles Davis' band in the late 1960s, he participated in the birth of the electric jazz fusion movement. In the 1970s, Corea founded the legendary jazz fusion group Return to Forever. Along with Herbie Hancock, McCoy Tyner and Keith Jarrett, Corea is one of the biggest modern jazz pianists. He continued musical collaborations with a diverse range of artists, exploring various musical styles. This broadcast features three performances that illustrate Chick Corea's many talents.

programme.title: Kirill Karabits, Russian National Orchestra & Mikhail Pletnev
programme.desc: Pianist Mikhail Pletnev is accompanied by the Russian National Orchestra led by Kirill Karabits in a performance of Camille Saint-Saëns's Piano Concerto No. 2, Op. 22. At its premiere in 1868, the orchestra was led by Anton Rubinstein, with the composer himself at the piano. The current concert was recorded at the Moscow Philharmonic Society and opens with a performance of Sergei Prokofiev's symphonic picture 'Dreams'. The concert was part of the Ninth Russian National Orchestra Grand Festival from 2017.

programme.title: Ballet of the Mariinsky Theatre
programme.desc: 'La Bayadère' is a three-act ballet by the French choreographer Marius Petipa. Set in 19th-century India, 'La Bayadère' tells the sad love story of the noble warrior Solor and his Nikia, a temple dancer or 'bayadère', who is poisoned by her rival, Gamzatti. The ballet features one of the most celebrated scenes of classical ballet, namely 'The Kingdom of the Shades'. In this iconic scene, Solor dreams, under the influence of opium, of reuniting with his beloved Nikia. This production of the ballet features the revised choreography by Vladimir Ponomarev and Vakhtang Chabukiani (1941), and includes dances by Konstantin Sergeyev and Nikolai Zubkovsky. The ballet's music, composed by Ludwig Minkus, is performed by the Mariinsky Orchestra under the direction of Boris Gruzin. Among the performers are Viktoria Tereshkina, Anastasia Matvienko, Vladimir Shklyarov, and Vladimir Ponomarev. This performance was recorded at the Mariinsky Theatre in St. Petersburg, Russia, in July 2014.

programme.title: Marina De Liso, Roberto Loreggian & Nicola Dal Maso
programme.sub-title: Vocal works by Monteverdi, Frescobaldi a. o.
programme.desc: The six-concert series “Io suono italiano” is dedicated to music of Italian composers and performed by Italian musicians on Italian instruments. The concert programs cover four centuries of music: from Girolamo Frescobaldi and Antonio Vivaldi to more contemporary music by Ennio Morricone and Azio Corghi. Each program presents more familiar pieces alongside lesser-known compositions. These performances were filmed at the atmospheric Teatro Sociale in Rovigo, Italy, in January 2021. In this program, Marina De Liso (soprano), Roberto Loreggian (harpsichord), and Nicola Dal Maso (violone) present vocal Baroque music. On the program are Benedetto Ferrari's Amanti io vi so dire, Barbara Strozzi's Lamento, Tradimento, and Che si può fare, Giovanni Felice Sances's Usurpator tiranno, Girolamo Frescobaldi's Partite sopra il Passacagli, and Se l'aura spira, Claudio Monteverdi's Ohimè ch'io cado, and Si dolce è il tormento.

programme.title: Chen Xue-Hong, Zhang Cheng, Chen Yunjie & Chen Sa
programme.sub-title: Piano works by Chopin, Scriabin, Schumann & Liszt
programme.desc: In recent years, a new generation of Chinese pianists has emerged on the international scene. But there are many more young Chinese artists, who the Académie France-Chine aims to enable to deepen their art by introducing them to and giving them a platform within French and European culture. Four of these artists are Chen Xue-Hong, Zhang Cheng, Chen Yunjie and Chen Sa, who made their joint debut in Paris in this unique concert at the Théâtre des Champs-Élysées that showcased their extraordinary talent. On the program are Chopin's Piano Sonata No. 2, Schumann's Piano Sonata No. 1, Scriabin's Piano Sonata No. 8 and Paysage (No. 3) and Mazeppa (No. 4) from Liszt's Études d'Exécution Transcendante. The concert closes with Messiaen's Regard de l'Esprit de la joie (No. 10) from Vingt regards sur l'Enfant-Jésus.
